<TITLE> Indian border guards kill Bangladeshi man </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chuadanga, May 05 (bdnews24.com)--- A Bangladeshi man was killed by the Indian border guards inside their territory on Tuesday night. Azad Mondol,32, from Nastipur village was shot by the guards at Thakurer Math in Nodia district of India. Commanding officer of the Chuadanga BDR battalion, Lt Col Sultan Ahmed said that Azad was returning from India along with some of his fellow cattle traders and was shot by BSF soldiers from Bijoypur camp under the 12 battalion. Azad died on the spot and the rest fled the scene, he added. The incident took place two kilometres inside Indian border, he said. BDR officer said that they are trying to get further details of the incident and the body is under the custody of BSF. bdn
